<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,150,1689]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,150,176]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Description.</emphasis>
Body generally chestnut brown, partly tinged with red in fresh specimens (
<figureCitation box="[1217,1310,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,181,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[165,1423,181,1847]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 6. Habitus images of conifer-inhabiting Pilophorus spp. (A–C) and Pherolepis spp. (D–H), live adults and 5th instar nymph (G). A. Pilophorus miyamotoi ♂. B. P. validicornis ♀ (image courtesy of M. Nozawa). C. P. tagoi ♀ (courtesy of M. Nozawa). D. Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp., ♂. E. Same, lateral view. F. Same, ♀. G. Same, 5th instar nymph, ♂. H. Pherolepis fasciatus ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596043/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
), elongateovoid in overall appearance, not constricted laterally (
<figureCitation box="[765,852,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,181,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[165,1423,181,1847]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 6. Habitus images of conifer-inhabiting Pilophorus spp. (A–C) and Pherolepis spp. (D–H), live adults and 5th instar nymph (G). A. Pilophorus miyamotoi ♂. B. P. validicornis ♀ (image courtesy of M. Nozawa). C. P. tagoi ♀ (courtesy of M. Nozawa). D. Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp., ♂. E. Same, lateral view. F. Same, ♀. G. Same, 5th instar nymph, ♂. H. Pherolepis fasciatus ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596043/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface with uniformly distributed, simple, reclining setae and silvery sericeous setae on head, dorsum and thoracic pleura. Head dark brown; head with eyes (1.3–1.4 times) wider than high; vertex relatively wide. Antenna somber yellowish brown; extreme apices of segments I and II sometimes darkened; segment II weakly clavate; segments III and IV grayish brown. Labium shiny chestnut brown, partly reddish, reaching subapical part of metacoxa. Pronotum shiny fuscous, with sparsely distributed sericeous setae anteriorly (or calli area); scutellum fuscous, shallowly and transversely rugose, with sparsely distributed sericeous setae; pleura shiny dark brown, partly tinged with red; scent efferent system smoky reddish brown, triangular, with rather small peritreme (
<figureCitation box="[768,873,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,309,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-72@35.[215,1372,309,1848]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 20. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus niger (A–C), P. tagoi (D), and Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp. (E–O). A, D, G. Left lateral habitus. B, I. Metatarsus. Right lateral habitus. C, L. Endosoma. E. Dorsal habitus. F. Left-dorsolateral habitus. H. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. J. Pygophore, dorsal view. K. Left paramere. M. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. N–O. Posterior wall of bursae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596083/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 20H</figureCitation>
). Hemelytron brown, somewhat matte; exocorium sometimes yellowish or reddish brown; membrane smoky brown, semitransparent laterally, with yellowish veins. All coxae creamy yellow, with reddish extreme bases (
<figureCitation box="[760,847,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,181,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[165,1423,181,1847]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 6. Habitus images of conifer-inhabiting Pilophorus spp. (A–C) and Pherolepis spp. (D–H), live adults and 5th instar nymph (G). A. Pilophorus miyamotoi ♂. B. P. validicornis ♀ (image courtesy of M. Nozawa). C. P. tagoi ♀ (courtesy of M. Nozawa). D. Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp., ♂. E. Same, lateral view. F. Same, ♀. G. Same, 5th instar nymph, ♂. H. Pherolepis fasciatus ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596043/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
); legs somber yellow; each femur sometimes weakly obscured but not distinctly darkened; apical part of tarsomere III brown; pretarsal structure as in 
<figureCitation box="[1226,1318,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,309,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-72@35.[215,1372,309,1848]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 20. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus niger (A–C), P. tagoi (D), and Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp. (E–O). A, D, G. Left lateral habitus. B, I. Metatarsus. Right lateral habitus. C, L. Endosoma. E. Dorsal habitus. F. Left-dorsolateral habitus. H. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. J. Pygophore, dorsal view. K. Left paramere. M. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. N–O. Posterior wall of bursae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596083/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 20I</figureCitation>
. Abdomen shiny fuscous, with ventral median part often reddish brown in both sexes. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1278,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox="[164,1436,601,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-179@26.[151,1436,597,1791]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Male (A–B) and female (C–D) genitalia of Phelorepis hizenicus n. sp. A. Pygophore with parameres. B. Endosoma (vesica). C. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. D. Same, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596065/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs 13</figureCitation>
A–B, 20J–L): Genital segment rather small, trapezoidal; phallotheca broad with a tapered apex (
<figureCitation box="[1069,1164,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,309,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-72@35.[215,1372,309,1848]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 20. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus niger (A–C), P. tagoi (D), and Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp. (E–O). A, D, G. Left lateral habitus. B, I. Metatarsus. Right lateral habitus. C, L. Endosoma. E. Dorsal habitus. F. Left-dorsolateral habitus. H. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. J. Pygophore, dorsal view. K. Left paramere. M. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. N–O. Posterior wall of bursae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596083/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 20J</figureCitation>
); left paramere sprayedout, with developed, spatula-shaped sensory lobe (
<figureCitation box="[715,820,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,309,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-72@35.[215,1372,309,1848]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 20. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus niger (A–C), P. tagoi (D), and Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp. (E–O). A, D, G. Left lateral habitus. B, I. Metatarsus. Right lateral habitus. C, L. Endosoma. E. Dorsal habitus. F. Left-dorsolateral habitus. H. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. J. Pygophore, dorsal view. K. Left paramere. M. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. N–O. Posterior wall of bursae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596083/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 20K</figureCitation>
); right paramere rather bulbous, with small hypophysis (
<figureCitation box="[160,268,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox="[164,1436,601,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-179@26.[151,1436,597,1791]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Male (A–B) and female (C–D) genitalia of Phelorepis hizenicus n. sp. A. Pygophore with parameres. B. Endosoma (vesica). C. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. D. Same, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596065/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
