<figureCitation box="[1157,1266,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox="[164,1436,601,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-179@26.[151,1436,597,1791]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Male (A–B) and female (C–D) genitalia of Phelorepis hizenicus n. sp. A. Pygophore with parameres. B. Endosoma (vesica). C. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. D. Same, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596065/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs 13B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1282,1331,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,309,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-72@35.[215,1372,309,1848]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 20. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus niger (A–C), P. tagoi (D), and Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp. (E–O). A, D, G. Left lateral habitus. B, I. Metatarsus. Right lateral habitus. C, L. Endosoma. E. Dorsal habitus. F. Left-dorsolateral habitus. H. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. J. Pygophore, dorsal view. K. Left paramere. M. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. N–O. Posterior wall of bursae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596083/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">20L</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[262,345,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox="[164,1436,601,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-179@26.[151,1436,597,1791]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Male (A–B) and female (C–D) genitalia of Phelorepis hizenicus n. sp. A. Pygophore with parameres. B. Endosoma (vesica). C. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. D. Same, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596065/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs 13</figureCitation>
C–D, 20M–O): Genital chamber with laterally thickened and folded sclerotized rings and narrow, concentric sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[380,489,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,309,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-72@35.[215,1372,309,1848]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 20. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus niger (A–C), P. tagoi (D), and Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp. (E–O). A, D, G. Left lateral habitus. B, I. Metatarsus. Right lateral habitus. C, L. Endosoma. E. Dorsal habitus. F. Left-dorsolateral habitus. H. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. J. Pygophore, dorsal view. K. Left paramere. M. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. N–O. Posterior wall of bursae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596083/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 20M</figureCitation>
); interramal lobe of posterior wall widely spinulate except for basal (anterior) margin (
<figureCitation box="[160,264,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,309,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-72@35.[215,1372,309,1848]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 20. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus niger (A–C), P. tagoi (D), and Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp. (E–O). A, D, G. Left lateral habitus. B, I. Metatarsus. Right lateral habitus. C, L. Endosoma. E. Dorsal habitus. F. Left-dorsolateral habitus. H. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. J. Pygophore, dorsal view. K. Left paramere. M. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. N–O. Posterior wall of bursae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596083/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 20N</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,150,1689]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,835,861]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Measurements.</emphasis>
